An angry mob in Kabba, Kogi State, has set an old police barracks ablaze following the alleged killing of a boy by a policeman. It was gathered that the the young boy was killed by a yet-to-be-identified police officer. The boy was alleged to have taken a sachet of pure water from the Policeman’s man’s car to drink but later had an argument with the Policeman before he was killed. NAWOJ Advocates Justice For Hanifa, Others Fire Guts LAMATA Terminal In Ajah The Kogi State Commissioner of Police, CP Edward Egbuka, who confirmed the latest development, said the Command is currently investigating the matter.